Shortly before the Easter holiday commenced learners and guests at Mitchell House witnessed the official handing over of an outdoor classroom donated by the St Engenas Zion Christian Church and the 2013 to 2015 matric learners that hosted a number of functions to raise funds. St Engenas Zion Christian Church Bishop Engenas Lekganyane officiated at the event and was accompanied by his wife, Magrett and officials of the church. During the short ceremony, guests were entertained by the church s band and the school choir. Information regarding the final cost of the project could not be obtained at time of going to print. Story and photos: BARRY VILJOEN &gt;&gt;barryv.observer@gmail.com Bishop Engenas Lekganyane, Head of St Engenas Zion Christian Church and Mitchell House Headmaster Andrew Cook at the official opening of the outdoor classroom last Friday. Bishop Engenas Lekganyane and his wife Magrett, Mitchell House Headmaster Andrew Cook and Director of Studies Claude Goeminne. Guests listen to the performance of the band of the St Engenas Zion Christian Church.